                     <interp inst="t18270913-284-defend2225" type="age" value="35"></interp>
                  </persName>
             and 
               <persName id="t18270913-284-defend2226" type="defendantName">
                  THOMAS 
                  BRACE
               <interp inst="t18270913-284-defend2226" type="surname" value="BRACE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-284-defend2226" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-284-defend2226" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-284-defend2226" type="age" value="55"></interp>
                  </persName>
             were indicted for <rs id="t18270913-284-off1581" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18270913-284-off1581" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-284-off1581" type="offenceSubcategory" value="simpleLarceny"></interp>
               stealing, on the <rs id="t18270913-284-cd1582" type="crimeDate">3d of August</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270913-284-off1581 t18270913-284-cd1582"></join>, 4 bushels of oats, value 12s.; 2 bushels of chaff, value 1s., and 1 sack, value 1s.
            </rs>, the goods of 
               <persName id="t18270913-284-victim2227" type="victimName">
                  Charles 
                  Batley
               <interp inst="t18270913-284-victim2227" type="surname" value="Batley"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-284-victim2227" type="given" value="Charles"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-284-victim2227" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270913-284-off1581 t18270913-284-victim2227"></join>
                  </persName>
            .</p>
               <p>CHARLES BATLEY. I <rs id="t18270913-284-viclabel1583" type="occupation">job horses for the coal merchants</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270913-284-victim2227 t18270913-284-viclabel1583"></join>. I have a stable at Mr. Beetham's wharf, near the canal at <placeName id="t18270913-284-crimeloc1584">Hoxton</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18270913-284-crimeloc1584" type="placeName" value="Hoxton"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18270913-284-crimeloc1584" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270913-284-off1581 t18270913-284-crimeloc1584"></join>. I missed some corn and this sack, which was in the granary about a fortnight at three weeks before the officer took the prisoner, I missed five quarters of corn in the space of a fortnight.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. CLARKSON. Q. Was it not mixed with peas? A. I do not know.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-284-person2228">
                  CHARLES 
                  MIELL
               <interp inst="t18270913-284-person2228" type="surname" value="MIELL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-284-person2228" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-284-person2228" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. On the 3d of August, about half-past two o'clock in the morning, I was coming over Kingsland-road bridge, and saw the prisoner with another man coming out of the prosecutor's stable - the prisoners had each a sack; the third man opened a door to see if any body was coming - he did not see me; he said something to the prisoners - they came into the road, and went into a stable belonging to Brace. I followed, and saw them throw down the loads in the stable. I pushed the door open, went in, and there saw Brace, who had been holding the door, so that we should not come in - he keeps a horse and cart. I asked him what they had got - he said a bit of corn and chaff for the horse - we took them in charge; another patrol went after the third man, but he was gone. I went and took Batley's horse-keeper, but he was discharged - here are the two sacks which I found in Brace's stable.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined. Q. Where were you when you saw them? A. By the wall, about thirty yards from the stable. I could see the door by the light of a fire from a coak burner. I saw them within two yards of the stable door; the third man was in the stable.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-284-person2229">
                  JOHN 
                  STEVENSON
               <interp inst="t18270913-284-person2229" type="surname" value="STEVENSON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-284-person2229" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-284-person2229" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was with Miell. I went and took the prisoners in Brace's stable.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined. Q. Were they not discharged on bail? A. Yes.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-284-person2230">
                  CHARLES 
                  BATLEY
               <interp inst="t18270913-284-person2230" type="surname" value="BATLEY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-284-person2230" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-284-person2230" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I have too many oats to miss any; both these sacks were in my stable, and one is my own. I have no doubt that the oats and chaff are mine - there is none there but what is mine.</p>

               <p>OSBORN's Defence. I met Brace on the road with two sacks - he told me to carry one which I did.</p>
               <p>BRACE's Defence. I bought the sack of chaff the overnight.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-284-person2231">
                  ROBERT 
                  EDWARDS
               <interp inst="t18270913-284-person2231" type="surname" value="EDWARDS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-284-person2231" type="given" value="ROBERT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-284-person2231" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a carman. I occasionally sell corn and chaff - I live in Kingsland-road. I sold Brace a sack of chaff - I cannot tell the day of the month, but it was the night before he was taken - I really believe this to be the same chaff. I sold him about five bushels.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-284-person2232">
                  JOHN 
                  SMITH
               <interp inst="t18270913-284-person2232" type="surname" value="SMITH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-284-person2232" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-284-person2232" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I lent Brace a sack five or six days before he was taken - this is it. I know it by the corner being tied, which I did - the name of Love is on it.</p>
               <p>OSBORN - <rs id="t18270913-284-verdict1585" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18270913-284-verdict1585" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 35.</p>
               <p>BRACE - <rs id="t18270913-284-verdict1586" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18270913-284-verdict1586" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 55.</p>
